secondly - to whoever said that slamming has to do with your shoulder slot is full of it.  Granted a slam is supposed to be done with your shoulder but the game does it according to what is in your off hand.  Example: I had a barbarian warrior with 2 langs...if i tried to bash it would say i needed a shield equipped obviously...as i was fighting a wisp in qey hills...i slammed it...i didnt have magic shoulders (unless bronze used to be magic which i doubt) but i did have a magic sword in my off hand and i hit the wisp...a little freaked out and thinking that being a higher level than the wisp allowed me to hit it without magic items, i disarmed the sword and found another wisp...needless to say the level thing was wrong and without the sword equiped i did nothing...as soon as i re-eqiupped the sword i could slam again...<BR>
